HEXAHEDRIZATION of a CUBE or a SPHERE
A KERNEL is subdivided into CUBSPN**3 cubes with an edge length of
CUBSPL/CUBSPN where CUBSPL is the length of the kernel.
CUBSPD is the total length of the kernel+layers formed from
the boundary of the kernel.
With the option SPHERE, the vertices of hexahedra are projected on
co-centric spheres of radii multiples of CUBSPL/CUBSPN,
after, in geometric ratio to pass from CUBSPL/CUBSPN to the last radius

GIVE CUBSPC>0 the NUMBER of LAYERS AROUND the KERNEL.
